# Ship the Cython sources into the sdist so a source install can rebuild the
# compiled extension. Without this the sdist omits `_filters_c/_inner.pyx`, so
# the default `python -m build` (wheel-from-sdist) and `pip install <sdist>`
# both fail to cythonize. The wheel carries the precompiled `.so` and needs
# none of these; only the sdist does. The generated `_inner.c` rides along
# automatically as the cythonized extension source. See docs/adr/0060-*.md.
#
# There are no `.pxd` files today; add `*.pxd` here alongside `*.pyx` if a
# Cython declaration file is ever introduced (setuptools warns on a glob that
# matches nothing, so it is not listed pre-emptively).
recursive-include aaanalysis *.pyx
